Here are the key topics in Spring MVC:
 
1. MVC Architecture
	• Model: Represents data and business logic
	• View: Handles data presentation
	• Controller: Manages user requests and workflow
2. DispatcherServlet
	• Front controller pattern
	• Central point for request handling
3. Controllers
	• @Controller annotation
	• Request mapping (@RequestMapping, @GetMapping, @PostMapping, etc.)
	• Handler methods
4. Request Mapping
	• URL pattern matching
	• HTTP method-specific mappings
5. Model and ModelAndView
	• Data passing between controller and view
6. View Resolution
	• ViewResolver interface
	• Different view technologies (JSP, Thymeleaf, FreeMarker)
7. Data Binding
	• Form handling
	• @ModelAttribute annotation
8. Validation
	• Bean Validation (JSR-303)
	• Custom validators
9. Exception Handling
	• @ExceptionHandler
	• Global exception handling
10. Interceptors
	• Pre-processing and post-processing of requests
11. REST Support
	• @RestController
	• @ResponseBody and @RequestBody
12. File Upload and Download
	• MultipartResolver
	• File handling utilities
13. Internationalization (i18n)
	• LocaleResolver
	• ResourceBundleMessageSource
14. Spring Security Integration
	• Authentication and authorization
15. Testing
	• Unit testing controllers
	• Integration testing with MockMvc
16. Configuration
	• Java-based (@Configuration)
	• XML-based
	• Spring Boot auto-configuration
 
Understanding these key topics provides a solid foundation for working with Spring MVC and developing robust web applications.
